As many as 1, 500 families at Elijah Barayi Village in Carletonville in the West Rand will be moving to their new homes on Sunday. The move comes after the Department of Human Settlements, Water and Sanitation Minister Lindiwe Sisulu issued a directive to fast track government housing projects to help mitigate the effects of the coronavirus pandemic. Courtesy #DStv403 CARLETONVILLE - As many as 1, 500 families at Elijah Barayi Village in Carletonville in the West Rand will be moving to their new homes on Sunday. READ: West Rand emergency housing put up, Sisulu takes aim at media The move comes after the Department of Human Settlements, Water and Sanitation Minister Lindiwe Sisulu issued a directive to fast track government housing projects to help mitigate the effects of the coronavirus pandemic. The minister said she is happy the project has come to this point particularly as winter closes in. "Most of the people who will be relocated will find themselves in comfortable accommodation throughout this winter and throughout the rest of the COVID period," she said. READ: West Rand declared COVID-19 hotspot The minister put out a call to all provincial governments to fast track their projects in order to assist in creating social distance to limit the spread of COVID-19. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.